-- Sinograin Halts Grain Trade to Stabilize Prices, China Business News Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T23:47:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/sinograin-halts-grain-trade-to-stabilize-prices-china-business-news-says.html
China Grain Reserves Corp., also
known as Sinograin, has temporarily halted grain trading
operations with the aim of stabilizing prices, China Business
News reported today, citing an unidentified person.  Sinograin stopped grain purchases when market prices are
higher than the minimum purchasing price, the report said,
citing the company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  